Applications available in English
<ol> SNP-Based Genetic Heterogeneity, &Psi;<br>
<ol>
SNP-based Genetic Heterogeneity, &Psi; was introduced by our lab and was published in Genetic Epidemiology. 
<br>
Briefly, &Psi; is a set of 2<sup>n</sup> variables that define frequency of 2<sup>n</sup>; haplotypes for n biallelic SNPs.
Using &Psi;, we introduced a new method to define linkage disequilibrium among any number of multiple SNPs (Dg). Also &Psi; enables us to infer the global maximum of haplotype frequency for a small number of SNPs. Although the regular EM algorithm is known to give a good estimate in the majority of cases, it is known to return a local maximum in rare occasions. The &Psi;-based method to infer haplotype frequency is free from this mis-convergence to a local maximum.
<br>
Five applications on &Psi; and its related method, Dg, and &Psi;-based inference of haplotype frequency, are available.
<br>
The first is an MS Excel file to infer haplotype frequency with &Psi;-based method for SNP pairs, "SNPpairPsi.xls".
<br>
The second is an Java application to infer haplotype frequency with &Psi;-based method for SNP pairs, "DerivativeEM3ForWeb".
<br>
The third is a calculator of &Psi; and Dg, "PsiDgForWeb". It calculates &Psi; and Dg from haplotype frequency data (downward calculation) and also infer haplotype frequency from unphased genotype data with calculation of corresponding &Psi; and Dg (upward calculation).
<br>
The fourth is a perl program to draw a picture of representative Dg values, DgDrawer.pl.
<br>
The fifth is a CGI-version of the forth perl program, CGI for DgDrawer.
<br>


